name: PARNASO #1 - The Finger of God
description:
The Finger of God, "Dedo de Deus" in portuguese, is probably the most famous geological monument of PARNASO and its highest peak. It can be seen from many near and far places but the best view is from Soberbo's viewpoint.

To feel the photo: It's mid morning in Rio's mountainous region, the sun is hot but the air is chilly and there's a moderate wind flowing all the time. It's a trip to gather with the family and chill out.

About the series: Pictures taken in and around the Serra dos Órgãos National Park ('Parque Nacional da Serra dos Órgãos' in portuguese or its abbreviation 'PARNASO'), located in the state of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, and covers a huge area across four municipalities.

Equipment: Nikon D5100 + Nikon AF-S DX NIKKOR 55-200mm f/4-5.6G ED VR
Location: Soberbo's Viewpoint - Teresópolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
